erage fraction\nof cores throughout the cycle changes by the same factor as the X-ray\nluminosity. The maxima of the cycle are characterized by a high percentage of\ncovering fraction of the flares, consistent with the fact that flaring events\nare seen in the corresponding short-term X-ray lightcurves predominately at the\ncycle maxima. The high X-ray emission throughout the cycle of Epsilon Eridani\nis thus explained by the high percentage of magnetic structures on its surface.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 25 Feb 2020 16:31:51 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-04-15"}
