ation of distances and proper motions. Finally, we detect\nthe bifurcation in the leading arm and report no significant difference between\nthe two branches, either in metallicity, kinematics or distance. We provide the\nlargest sample of RR Lyrae candidates of Sagittarius, which can be used as an\ninput for a spectroscopic follow-up or as a reference for the new generation of\nmodels of the stream through the interpolators in distance and velocity that we\nhave constructed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 25 Feb 2020 19:07:21 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 23 Jul 2020 19:35:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-07-27"}
